item.title: Foster carer on sex abuse charges
item.description: A Sydney man has been charged over the alleged ongoing sexual abuse of a teenage girl in the city’s south west.

item.title: Virus hits multiple stores and gym
item.description: Sydney residents are on high alert after NSW Health released a flurry of notices overnight about positive cases visiting businesses around the CBD, including a gym, Kmart and an Apple store.

item.title: Cancer fighter “fights baddies” with NSW cops
item.description: Six-year-old Mitchell Ray has always wanted to “fight baddies”.

item.title: Ex-RSL president wins fraud appeal
item.description: A former NSW RSL president has had his fraud conviction quashed after a judge ruled he wasn’t using the organisation’s money on “French champagne and strip clubs.”

item.title: Sydney quarantine hotel evacuated
item.description: A medi-hotel housing repatriated Australians is being evacuated after the hotel failed an audit.

item.title: Norman wants Griffin as Dragons coach
item.description: St George Illawarra five-eighth Corey Norman wants to play under his former Brisbane coach Anthony Griffin at the Dragons.

item.title: Verdict in uni academic’s stabbing trial
item.description: A university academic has been found not guilty of stabbing a group of teenagers in a Sydney park after a jury found he was suffering from severe mental illness at the time.

item.title: Filthy conditions made hotel guest ‘vomit’
item.description: A hotel guest has told of how her dirty and dusty quarantine hotel left her pleading for “fresh air” and exacerbated her asthma so badly she “vomited”.

item.title: Greens leader’s final message
item.description: Outgoing Greens leader Richard Di Natale has called for a reset of national politics as he today bid farewell to the federal parliament.

item.title: Man jailed for $18m drug lab
item.description: An Adelaide man caught with more than $18 million worth of ice at a lab set up in a suburban home has been jailed.
